Definition
CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system.
 It allows you to arrange elements in rows and columns.
Grid works on the parent element.
How to Activate Grid
.container {
 display: grid;
}


Defining Columns
Fixed Width Columns
grid-template-columns: 200px 200px 200px;

Creates three columns with fixed width.

Using Fraction (fr)
grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;

fr means “fraction of available space”.
2fr takes more space than 1fr.

Using repeat()
grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);

Creates four equal columns.

Complete Grid Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
 <style>
   .container {
     display: grid;
     grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
     gap: 10px;
   }

   .box {
     background-color: black;
     color: white;
     padding: 20px;
     text-align: center;
   }
 </style>
</head>
<body>

 <div class="container">
   <div class="box">1</div>
   <div class="box">2</div>
   <div class="box">3</div>
   <div class="box">4</div>
 </div>

</body>
</html>





